the NHS Business Services Authority:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Cost (£)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>1,469,034</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>1,566,587</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>1,594,957</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","44393","2016-09-12T13:18:30.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573710/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573710/answer",,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-02","NHS Low Income Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the overall cost of administering the NHS Low Income Scheme was in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","44396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573711","Department of Health","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Minimum Practice Income Guarantee is being phased out because it is inequitable. Under the system, two practices in the same area and serving very similar populations may be paid very different amounts of money per registered patient.</p><p> </p><p>The payments are being phased out over seven years, to allow practices time to adjust to the new arrangements. The funds released are being added to the ‘global sum’ – the basic payments made to all General Medical Services practices, which are based on numbers of patients and key determinants of practice workload, such as the age and health needs of patients.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England, which is responsible for commissioning primary care services, is committed to supporting the small number of practices that are significantly affected by the changes.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-09-12T13:15:58.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573711/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573711/answer",,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-02","General Practitioners: Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of his Department's policy to reduce the minimum practice income guarantee.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","44388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573712","Department of Health","false","2016-09-12","<p>No such research has been undertaken.</p><p> </p><p>Provision of infertility treatment, as for all health services they commission, is decided by local clinical commissioning groups. They must have regard to the guidelines on the provision of NHS funded infertility services, published by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence in October 2014 but they must also take into account the heath needs and priorities of the local population when determining the range and level of services they are able to provide. For that reason, provision of services will vary in response to local needs.</p><p> </p><p>Representatives from NHS England, the British Fertility Society and Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority are looking at how commissioning of in vitro fertilisation services could be improved.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-09-12T14:29:45.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573712/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573712/answer",,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-02","Fertility: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research his Department has conducted on investment trends in tertiary fertility services; and what guidance he offers to clinical commissioning groups proposing to decommission IVF services.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","44420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573713","Department of Health","false","2016-09-12","<p>These data are not collected centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","44126","2016-09-12T16:19:55.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573713/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573713/answer",,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-02","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department holds information on the number of people in (a) England, (b) Wales, (c) Scotland and (d) Northern Ireland with insurance who received NHS treatment following a road traffic accident in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","44168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573714","Department of Health","false","2016-09-12","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The General Practice Forward View, published in April 2016, announced a commitment to 5,000 doctors in general practice and a minimum of 5,000 other staff working in general practice by 2020-21. This will include investment in an extra 3,000 mental health therapists to work in primary care by 2020 to support localities to expand the Improving Access to Psychological Therapies programme. This amounts to an average of a full time therapist for every 2-3 typical sized GP practices.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-09-12T16:47:13.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573714/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573714/answer",,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-02","General Practitioners: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many GP practices in England have access to a mental health worker to support patients.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","44189"
