mer budget 2015.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","44401 ; 44402 ; 44413 ; 44558","2016-09-12T12:54:02.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573918/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573918/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Department for Work and Pensions: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has for the future role of employees and contractors of his Department who are working on the compilation and administration of data related to the provision of free television licences to people over 75 years of age.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","44400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573919","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>The Department updated its strategy for releasing official statistics on Universal Credit (UC) in February 2016. As outlined in the strategy, officials are currently assessing the data for UC and will only release information once the necessary quality assurance work has taken place. These statistics will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for official statistics.</p><p> </p><p>Universal Credit official statistics and the Departments release strategy can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-08T12:28:26.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573919/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573919/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when his Department plans to publish data on the number of (a) low, (b) medium and (c) high level sanctions applied to universal credit claimants (i) before and (ii) after challenges.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573920","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>ESA claimants who are found fit for work and are waiting for their mandatory reconsideration application to be decided, are eligible to claim JSA. This is the right benefit for those who are capable of work, with Jobcentre work coaches fully supporting these claimants during this period - and the statistics released on 8 September show that this period is now a relatively short one – the median average being around 9 days.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-12T13:30:24.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573920/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573920/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on claimants of no longer being eligible to receive employment and support allowance payments at the assessment rate when undergoing a mandatory reconsideration of a work capability assessment.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573921","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>The number of Disability Employment Advisers employed by the Department for Work and Pensions is 263 at July 2016.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-08T11:47:07.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573921/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573921/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Jobcentre Plus: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disability employment advisers are employed by Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573922","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-12T11:17:37.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573922/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573922/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many mandatory reconsiderations for personal independence payments have resulted in a revised decision as a result of further evidence in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573923","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>Individuals in receipt of PIP before the age of 65 will continue to receive PIP as long as they continue to meet the eligibility criteria. This mirrors Disability Living Allowance, the benefit that preceded PIP. Anyone that becomes disabled after the age of 65 will be able to claim Attendance Allowance.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-12T14:46:12.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573923/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573923/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Attendance Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of the introduction of personal independence payments on future rates of claims for attendance allowance.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573924","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>Short Term Benefit Advances (STBAs) are payments on account of benefit. The majority of STBAs are awarded to people in the period before their benefit is first due to be paid, but STBAs can also be paid where a change of circumstances significantly increases the amount of benefit due. STBAs are predominately paid to people claiming Income Support, Employment and Support Allowance and Jobseeker’s Allowance. They are not available to people claiming Universal Credit.</p><p>Between April 2015 and March 2016, there were 218,592 STBA applications in Great Britain as a whole, with monthly variations ranging from 17,188 in September 2015 to 21,529 in February 2016, but with no downward trend at the year end. In Scotland, there were 26,322 applications over the same period, with monthly variations ranging from 1,462 in November 2015 to 3,022 in April 2015, with a clear downward trend at the year end.</p><p>As the roll-out of Universal Credit to all new claimants progresses, we anticipate a corresponding decline in the number of STBA applications.</p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions continues to advertise the availability of STBAs through the gov.uk website, with information posters and leaflets in Jobcentres nationwide.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-12T12:45:34.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573924/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573924/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the reasons for the decline in Short Term Benefit Advance applications in (a) Scotland and (b) the UK between February 2015 and March 2016.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573925","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>There has been no statutory requirement to make a benefit decision within a specified time since 1998. This applies equally to a claim for benefit, an application for review and, since it was introduced in April 2013, an application for Mandatory Reconsideration. Decisions are made without delay – whilst giving claimants every opportunity to provide new and additional evidence to support their application.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-12T11:02:01.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573925/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573925/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on claimants of having no timescale within which his Department must return a mandatory reconsideration decision to the claimant.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573926","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-08T15:35:52.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573926/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573926/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average number of days was from the posting of a medical certificate by a claimant in support of an employment and support allowance claim to the day his Department acknowledged receipt of that certificate in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573927","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-08T11:51:35.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573927/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573927/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time taken was to process hardship payments between the day the application was made and the day the claimant received the payment for sanctioned (a) jobseeker's allowance and (b) employment and support allowance claimants before reviews, reconsiderations or appeals for the period between 1 July and 31 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573928","Cabinet Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-09-12T14:54:50.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573928/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573928/answer","PQ 44495 final.pdf","PQ 44495 final.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Employment Rate","UKSA Letter to Member - Employment Rate","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573928/answer",,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-09-02","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate his Department has made of the employment rate for disabled working people in each year from 2010 to 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","44495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573929","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>All assessment centres meet accessibility standards under the Equality Act 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Before attending an assessment, claimants are given the opportunity to alert the assessment provider to any additional requirements they may have and the providers will endeavour to meet any such reasonable requests.</p><p> </p><p>If a claimant is unable to travel to, or access an assessment centre as a result of their health condition or impairment, a home visit may be offered.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","44491","2016-09-08T15:29:22.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573929/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573929/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Social Security Benefits: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of accessibility of assessment centres for work capability assessment and personal independence payments consultations for people using larger or bariatric wheelchairs.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","44490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573930","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-08","<p>All assessment centres meet accessibility standards under the Equality Act 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Before attending an assessment, claimants are given the opportunity to alert the assessment provider to any additional requirements they may have and the providers will endeavour to meet any such reasonable requests.</p><p> </p><p>If a claimant is unable to travel to, or access an assessment centre as a result of their health condition or impairment, a home visit may be offered.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","44490","2016-09-08T15:29:24.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573930/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573930/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Social Security Benefits: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to ensure assessment centres for work capability assessment and personal independence payment consultations are fully accessible to people using different kinds of mobility assistance devices.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","44491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573931","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>The data below states the Average Speed of Answer for all UC calls for the period 1 January 2016 – 30 June 2016.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Universal Credit Average Speed of Answer</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Average Speed of Answer</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>January 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:09</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>February 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:03</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>March 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:01</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>April 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:44</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>May 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:24</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>June 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:41</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>00:02:22</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Data source: Operational Management Information System (OPMIS)</p><p>It would be a disproportionate cost to compute the median in each month, and the breakdown by waiting time intervals.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-12T12:06:10.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573931/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573931/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Universal Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average and median waiting time is for users calling the universal credit helpline; and how many calls to that helpline were answered in (a) less than five, (b) between five and 10, (c) between 10 and 15, (d) between 15 and 20 and (e) more than thirty minutes between 1 January and 30 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573932","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>This information can be found on the Contract Finder website - please see the below link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-12T12:55:58.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573932/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573932/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the value is of the contract between his Department and SCC for providing server support for the universal credit portal.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573933","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-12","<p>Whenever a service problem is identified the Department always prioritises claimants first ensuring their payments are not interrupted. In this instance the outage impacted only 24 of the 712 Jobcentres across Great Britain and none of the claimants impacted experienced a delay in their payments.</p><p>The performance of all systems is continuously monitored on many resilient servers and in the event of an outage an immediate impact assessment is made and appropriate action taken to ensure normal service is resumed at the earliest possible opportunity and the impact on claimants is minimised.</p><p>We continually assess the performance of our suppliers, and underlying engineering, to ensure systems are available to meet the needs of claimants and the Department. With the exception of this isolated supplier outage the performance of the UC portal has been higher than expected, however, further improvements to resilience were already under active consideration as part of preparing for UC Full Service national expansion.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","44473 ; 44510","2016-09-12T10:54:57.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573933/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573933/answer",,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-02","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans are in place to ensure that a server issue with the universal credit portal does not reoccur.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","44472"
