"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574159","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>For the periods we have full information [FY 13-14, 14-15 &amp; 15-16], a total of £243 million in funding was distributed to the following local authorities and gateway authorities, to support unaccompanied asylum seeking children. [This data is taken from unpublished local management information that is not subject to national statistics protocols and is therefore subject to change]. [Table]</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-09-12T15:20:33.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574159/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574159/answer","PQ 44745 - Table.doc","PQ 44745 - Table.doc","Local Authorities support -asylum seeking children","Local Authorities support -asylum seeking children","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574159/answer","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574159/answer/previousversion/9603","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/members/1562","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-02","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much funding to support unaccompanied asylum seeking children was provided to each (a) local authority and (b) gateway authority in (i) 2013-14, (ii) 2014-15, (iii) 2015-16, and (iv) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","44745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574160","Home Office","false","2016-09-07","<p>Government Ministers and officials engage with a wide range of stakeholders.</p><p>The Prime Minister has been clear that she wants to protect the status of EU nationals here. The only circumstances in which that would not be possible are if British citizens’ rights in other EU Member States were not protected in return.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-09-07T15:01:27.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574160/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574160/answer",,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-02","EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she has had with people from other EU countries living in the UK since the EU referendum on their right to live in the UK after the UK's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","44680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574161","Home Office","false","2016-09-12","<p>We have worked closely with our COMPASS Providers to improve property standards and over the lifetime of the contract quality standards have increased. Where issues with accommodation are discovered we work with our contractors to ensure issues are quickly addressed. When they are not we can and do impose sanctions and seek remedial plans to drive improvement. Through continued engagement with service users and accommodation providers and regular property inspections the Home Office will continue to ensure asylum accommodation is adequate.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-09-12T15:26:20.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574161/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574161/answer",,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-02","Compass Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans the Government has to improve the provision of asylum accommodation.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","44681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574162","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-09","<p>As noted in the Answer of 13 April 2013 to Question 151281, DFID funded two assessments on glacial melt in the Himalayan region. It has since piloted a method of assessing glaciers in the region using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAV). The studies indicate that the Himalayan glaciers have been shrinking overall at 0.4-0.5% per year since the 1950s. The studies are available on DFID’s Research for Development website.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-09-09T13:33:35.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574162/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574162/answer",,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-02","Tibet: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 11 May 2016 to Question 36578, what the findings relevant to Tibet were of her Department's-funded assessments of glacial melt and rivers in the Himalayas.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","44791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574163","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-12","<p>The UK Government is playing a leading role in improving energy access in developing countries, including through our Energy Africa campaign which is working with solar firms to help them access the finance they need to expand their businesses, create jobs and help reach millions of people in Africa without electricity access.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-09-12T15:19:22.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574163/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574163/answer",,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-02","Developing Countries: Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if her Department will increase investment in decentralised renewable energy in areas where it will benefit the world's poorest people.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","44756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574164","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-09","<p>The humanitarian situation in South Sudan remains dire. More than 2.4 million people are displaced; over 785,000 of them to neighbouring countries as refugees. 4.8 million South Sudanese people, almost half of the population, are at risk of severe food insecurity. Although famine has not yet been declared, there is a looming risk in parts of Unity State. Through DFID, the UK remains the second largest bilateral donor to South Sudan.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-09-09T10:54:29.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574164/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574164/answer",,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-02","South Sudan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the humanitarian situation in South Sudan; what estimate she has made of the number of (a) refugees, (b) displaced people and (c) people with severe malnutrition in that country.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","44783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574165","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Justice Secretary is clear that safety is fundamental to the proper functioning of our justice system and a vital part of our reform plans. There are a number of factors, including the availability of drugs in prisons, which must be tackled in order to make our prisons safe and places of rehabilitation.</p><p> </p><p>We have introduced tough new laws which will see those who smuggle packages over prison walls, including new psychoactive substances, face up to two years in prison. Those who involve themselves in the distribution of drugs in our prisons should know that they could face prosecution and extra time behind bars. We have a range of security measures and searching techniques in place to detect drugs, and to prevent smuggling into prisons.</p><p> </p><p>I am looking closely at this important issue, and will be setting our further plans in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","44392","2016-09-12T14:42:06.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574165/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574165/answer",,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-02","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps her Department is taking to combat the supply of drugs into prisons.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","44844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574166","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-09-07","<p>I am committed to making the process of going to court simpler, easier, and more sympathetic to victims. My department’s court reform programme will make sure victims and witnesses, both male and female, continue to be treated with respect throughout the process. For example, the digitisation of the courts services is having a positive impact on victims by providing the ability to give video evidence rather than facing the trauma of attending court.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2016-09-07T16:16:25.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574166/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/574166/answer",,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-02","Victims and Witnesses: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans she has to ensure appropriate arrangements are made available to safeguard vulnerable women who participate in criminal justice proceedings.","false","Biography information for Mims Davies","Eastleigh","Mims Davies","44751"
